RIFT VALLEY FEVER - SOMALIA
*****************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Rift Valley fever - Kenya & Somalia: RFI 980121215305
Date: Thu, 22 Jan 1998 18:27:41 -0500
From: Martin Hugh-Jones

Having good graduate students with connections helps ... I spoke with Dr
Abdullahi Kalif, now in Minnesota, who then spoke with his close colleagues
in Somalia.
Dr Mohamed Yussuf, MD, in Hargeisa says that his British medical colleagues
have clinically diagnosed haemorrhagic RVF in patients in that northern
Somali city. Presumably samples have been taken for laboratory confirmation
but until then it is only a presumption. Similar cases are occurring
throughout the Ogaden.
Dr. Mohamoud Issa, MD, Kismayu, told Abdullahi that the haemorrhagic RVF is
widespread in the Lower and Middle Juba (valley) regions. At first they had
also thought it was anthrax because of the bleeding. The case fatality rate
has been high.
The rumours of RVF in Hargeisa appear to have substance but still await
confirmation.
--
