[2
Date: Thu, 22 Jan 1998 10:26:05 -0500
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: Deutsche Presse-Agentur, 22 Jan 1998

According to reports gained by DPA in Mogadishu, there is an increase in
the number of deaths due to Rift Valley Fever, just as cholera deaths are
decreasing from 20 percent to 2 percent fatality.
During the past week: Lower Jubba region, including the towns of Dhobey,
Luq and Bulo Hawo: 105 deaths.
Local leaders are pleading for help from international aid agencies on the
RVF situation and credit outside agencies for the drop in the cholera deaths.
